<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1804" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1804">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/146</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I have reliable information Leguistas have considered having him sworn in
                            as President and seek asylum at the Legation. Under such tactical move
                            should it be given? Conference failed to reach an understanding;
                            proposals discussed include resignation of both Leguia and Junta and
                            general elections; negotiations continue.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>